\begin{definition*}[Minimal elements]
    {}
    $\Min \colon \posPA \to \posAA$ is the map that sends a subset~$\subA$ of a \SY{poset} to the minimal elements of that subset (those elements~$\setAel \setin \subA$ such that~$\setAel \posAleq \setBel$ for all~$\setBel \setin \subA$).
    In formulas:
    \begin{equation*}
        \defmapperiodset{\Min}{\posPA}{\posAA}{\subA}{\makesett{
                \setCel\setin \subA\colon
                \vmiddle{
                    \prftree{
                        \setDel\setin \subA
                    }{
                        \setDel\posAleq \setCel
                    }{
                        \setCel=\setDel
                    }
                }
            }}
    \end{equation*}
    Note that~$\Min(\subA)$ could be empty.
\end{definition*}
